  "prompt": "How come Harry can see the Thestrals after his fourth year and not before that?",
  "response": "In the Harry Potter series, Thestrals can only be seen by those who have witnessed death. Harry was present when Cedric Diggory was killed by Voldemort at the end of the Triwizard Tournament during his fourth year at Hogwarts. Before that moment, although Harry had witnessed his parents' deaths when he was a baby, he was too young to have a clear memory or understanding of death at that time. Therefore, he could not see Thestrals before his fourth year. Once he witnessed Cedric's death, he gained the ability to perceive these magical creatures.",
